comments: Abolished 1.4.1933 and added to the parish of Bramber.

In 1894 the East Sussex part of the parish of Edburton became 
    the separate parish of Fulking, so that thereafter Edburton was wholly in West 
    Sussex. Abolished 1.4.1933 and added to the parish of Upper Beeding.

Created 1894 from the East Sussex part of the parish of Edburton. 
    See also Table 2, note (g).

Abolished 1.10.1910 and added to the parish of Shoreham by 
    Sea.

Abolished 1.4.1928 and added to the parish of Brighton. See 
    also Table 2, note (d).

Abolished 31.3.1928 and added to the parish of Portslade 
    by Sea.

Created 1.4.1898 from the part of the parish of Portslade in Portslade 
    by Sea Urban District. See also Table 2, note (h).

Abolished 1.4.1928 and added to the parish of Brighton. See 
    also Table 2, note (d).

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Preston. Abolished 
    1.4.1928 and added to the parish of Hove.
Created 1.10.1910 out of the parishes of New Shoreham, Old Shorehm and Lancing. See also Table 2, note (i).

That part which until 1.4.1933 formed part of the parish of 
    Sompting. See also Table 2, note (j).
